#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.26:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.26:0.2"
msgid "3. Sattāvāsavagga"
msgstr "3. Abodes of Sentient Beings"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 26. Silāyūpasutta → silāyūpopamasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.26:0.3"
msgid "26. Silāyūpasutta"
msgstr "26. The Simile of the Stone Pillar"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.403"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: () → (evaṃ me sutaṃ) (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.26:1.1"
msgid "() "
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "an9.26:1.2"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca candikāputto rājagahe viharanti "
"veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. VAR: () → (āvuso …pe… etadavoca) (bj)
msgctxt "an9.26:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā candikāputto bhikkhū āmantesi ():"
msgstr "There Venerable Candikāputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an9.26:1.4"
msgid "“devadatto, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr "“Reverends, Devadatta teaches the mendicants like this:"

# See BB’s note on variant readings. It seems to me that the distinction between cetasa and pannaya paricita is hinting at the distinction between ceto and pannavimutti.
msgctxt "an9.26:1.5"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ "
"veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""
"‘When a mendicant’s mind is solidified by heart, it’s appropriate for them "
"to say:"

msgctxt "an9.26:1.6"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’”’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.26:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ candikāputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Sāriputta said to him:"

msgctxt "an9.26:2.2"
msgid "“na kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Candikāputta, Devadatta does not teach the mendicants like that."

msgctxt "an9.26:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ "
"veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:2.4"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:2.5"
msgid "Evañca kho, āvuso, candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr "He teaches like this:"

msgctxt "an9.26:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ "
"bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""
"‘When a mendicant’s mind is well consolidated by heart, it’s appropriate for "
"them to say:"

msgctxt "an9.26:2.7"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’”’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.26:3.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā candikāputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "an9.26:3.2"
msgid "“devadatto, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ "
"veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.4"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.5"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ candikāputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.6"
msgid "“na kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.7"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ "
"veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.8"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.9"
msgid "Evañca kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.10"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ "
"bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:3.11"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.26:4.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā candikāputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "And for a third time Venerable Candikāputta addressed the mendicants …"

msgctxt "an9.26:4.2"
msgid "“devadatto, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ "
"veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:4.4"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:4.5"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ candikāputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Sāriputta said to him:"

msgctxt "an9.26:4.6"
msgid "“na kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ evaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Candikāputta, Devadatta does not teach the mendicants like that."

msgctxt "an9.26:4.7"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā citaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ bhikkhuno kallaṃ "
"veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:4.8"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:4.9"
msgid "Evañca kho, āvuso candikāputta, devadatto bhikkhūnaṃ dhammaṃ deseti:"
msgstr "He teaches like this:"

msgctxt "an9.26:4.10"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti, tassetaṃ "
"bhikkhuno kallaṃ veyyākaraṇāya—"
msgstr ""
"‘When a mendicant’s mind is well consolidated by heart, it’s appropriate for "
"them to say:"

msgctxt "an9.26:4.11"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’”’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.404"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.26:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, āvuso, bhikkhuno cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant’s mind well consolidated with heart?"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.2"
msgid "‘Vītarāgaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"The mind is well consolidated with heart when they know: ‘My mind is without "
"greed.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.3"
msgid "‘vītadosaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr "… ‘My mind is without hate.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.4"
msgid "‘vītamohaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr "… ‘My mind is without delusion.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.5"
msgid "‘asarāgadhammaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to become greedy.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.6"
msgid "‘asadosadhammaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to become hateful.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.7"
msgid "‘asamohadhammaṃ me cittan’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to become deluded.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.8"
msgid ""
"‘anāvattidhammaṃ me cittaṃ kāmabhavāyā’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to return to rebirth in the sensual realm.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.9"
msgid ""
"‘anāvattidhammaṃ me cittaṃ rūpabhavāyā’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"… ‘My mind is not liable to return to rebirth in the realm of luminous form.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.10"
msgid ""
"‘anāvattidhammaṃ me cittaṃ arūpabhavāyā’ti cetasā cittaṃ suparicitaṃ hoti."
msgstr "… ‘My mind is not liable to return to rebirth in the formless realm.’"

msgctxt "an9.26:5.11"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ sammā vimuttacittassa kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno bhusā cepi cakkhuviññeyyā "
"rūpā cakkhussa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, nevassa cittaṃ pariyādiyanti;"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant’s mind is rightly freed like this, even if compelling "
"sights come into the range of vision they don’t occupy their mind."

msgctxt "an9.26:5.12"
msgid ""
"amissīkatamevassa cittaṃ hoti ṭhitaṃ āneñjappattaṃ, vayaṃ cassānupassati."
msgstr ""
"The mind remains unaffected. It is steady, imperturbable, observing "
"disappearance."

# I use feet rather than metres as the length is still approxiamately correct, and it retains the numerical symbolism.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.405"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.26:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, silāyūpo soḷasakukkuko."
msgstr "Suppose there was a stone pillar, sixteen feet long."

msgctxt "an9.26:6.2"
msgid "Tassassu aṭṭha kukkū heṭṭhā nemaṅgamā, aṭṭha kukkū upari nemassa."
msgstr "Eight feet were buried underground, and eight above ground."

msgctxt "an9.26:6.3"
msgid ""
"Atha puratthimāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi, neva naṃ "
"saṅkampeyya na sampavedheyya;"
msgstr ""
"And violent storms were to blow up out of the east, the west, the north, and "
"the south."

msgctxt "an9.26:6.4"
msgid "atha pacchimāya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:6.5"
msgid "atha uttarāya …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.26:6.6"
msgid ""
"atha dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya āgaccheyya bhusā vātavuṭṭhi, neva naṃ "
"saṅkampeyya na sampavedheyya."
msgstr "They couldn’t make it tremor and tremble and quake."

msgctxt "an9.26:6.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an9.26:6.8"
msgid "Gambhīrattā, āvuso, nemassa, sunikhātattā silāyūpassa."
msgstr ""
"It’s because that boundary pillar is firmly embedded, with deep foundations."

msgctxt "an9.26:6.9"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, sammā vimuttacittassa bhikkhuno bhusā cepi "
"cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā cakkhussa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, nevassa cittaṃ "
"pariyādiyanti;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant’s mind is rightly freed like this, even if "
"compelling sights come into the range of vision they don’t occupy their mind."

msgctxt "an9.26:6.10"
msgid ""
"amissīkatamevassa cittaṃ hoti ṭhitaṃ āneñjappattaṃ, vayaṃ cassānupassati."
msgstr ""
"The mind remains unaffected. It is steady, imperturbable, observing "
"disappearance."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.26:7.1"
msgid "Bhusā cepi sotaviññeyyā saddā …"
msgstr "If even compelling sounds …"

msgctxt "an9.26:7.2"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …"
msgstr "smells …"

msgctxt "an9.26:7.3"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā …"
msgstr "tastes …"

msgctxt "an9.26:7.4"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā …"
msgstr "touches …"

msgctxt "an9.26:7.5"
msgid ""
"manoviññeyyā dhammā manassa āpāthaṃ āgacchanti, nevassa cittaṃ pariyādiyanti;"
msgstr ""
"and thoughts come into the range of the mind they don’t occupy the mind."

msgctxt "an9.26:7.6"
msgid ""
"amissīkatamevassa cittaṃ hoti ṭhitaṃ āneñjappattaṃ, vayaṃ cassānupassatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"The mind remains unaffected. It is steady, imperturbable, observing "
"disappearance.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.26:7.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
